---
// Full-bleed visual band: plugin graph imagery.
---

<section
  id="pipeline"
  data-section="pipeline"
  class="ad-reveal border-paper-200/6 relative left-1/2 my-6 w-screen max-w-[100vw] scroll-mt-28 -translate-x-1/2 border-y sm:my-8"
  aria-labelledby="pipeline-heading"
>
  <div
    class="group relative min-h-[200px] overflow-hidden sm:min-h-[240px] md:min-h-[280px]"
  >
    <img
      src="/images/section-pipeline.png"
      alt=""
      class="ad-pipeline-slow h-full min-h-[200px] w-full object-cover object-center opacity-80 transition duration-500 group-hover:opacity-95"
      loading="lazy"
    />
    <div
      class="from-ink-1000/88 via-ink-1000/55 absolute inset-0 bg-linear-to-r to-ink-1000/88"
      aria-hidden="true"
    />
    <div
      class="absolute inset-0 flex flex-col items-center justify-center px-4 text-center"
    >
      <h2
        id="pipeline-heading"
        class="text-paper-50 font-display text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-balance sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl"
      >
        One core.<span
          class="text-evidence-300/95"
        > Many sources.</span>
      </h2>
      <p
        class="text-paper-200/80 mt-3 max-w-xl text-pretty text-sm sm:text-base"
      >
        Adapters and plugins turn webhooks and APIs into a single task shape—so the agent always runs
        the same way, no matter which tool rang the bell.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
